definition.value: A glycopentaosylceramide having beta-D-GlcA-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the pentasaccharide component; isolated from human sciatic nerves and cauda equina.

A dimethylpyrimido[4,5-b][1,4]benzodiazepin-6-one carrying at C-2 on the pyrimidine ring a [2-ethoxy-4-(4-hydroxypiperidin-1-yl)phenyl]amino substituent.  It is an inhibitor of the BMK1 kinase pathway.
Any three-ring heterocyclic compound with a skeleton consisting of a pyrimidine ring fused to a benzodiazepine bicycle.

A  sialotriaosylceramide that is N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-N-acylsphingosine in which the acyl group on the sphingosine nitrogen is octadecanoyl. A constituent of natural ganglioside GM2.
A dicarboxylic acid comprising 8-hydroxy-2-oxabicyclo[3.3.1]non-6-ene having carboxy groups placed at the 3- and 5-positions.
Polyoxin C in which the primary amino group has been condensed with D-tryptophan to form a peptide bond.

The oxime resulting from the formal condensation of 2-methyl-2-(methylsulfanyl)propanal with hydroxylamine. Addition of the oxime group to methyl isocyanate forms the final step in the synthesis of the systemic insecticide aldicarb.
An organophosphate oxoanion derived from 2-O-(6-phosphono-alpha-D-mannosyl)-D-glyceric acid by removal of the two protons from the phosphate group and the proton from the carboxylic acid group.
Dianion of alpha-D-mannose 6-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
Any benzimidazole substituted at the 1 position by erythrose.
An anion formed by deprotonation of at least one peptide carboxy group.
The univalent carboacyl group formed by loss of -OH from the carboxy group of salicylic acid.
The univalent carboacyl group formed by loss of -OH from the carboxy group of N-salicyloyl-L-serine.
The univalent carboacyl group formed by loss of -OH from the carboxy group of 2-(2-hydroxyphenyl)-4,5-dihydro-1,3-oxazole-4-carboxylic acid.
Any N-oxide of a purine or purine derivative.
Tetracarboxylate anion of dipyrromethane cofactor; major species at pH 7.3.
A 3,1-benzoxazin-1,4-dione having an N-methyl substituent and a nitro group at the 7-position.
Dicarboxylate anion of ferroheme b; major species at pH 7.3.
A disaccharide derivative consisting of two 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranonosyl units joined via an alpha-(2->8)-linkage with an O-allyl group at the anomeric centre.
A disaccharide derivative consisting of two 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranonosyl units joined via an alpha-(2->4)-linkage with an O-allyl group at the anomeric centre.
The (R)-enantiomer of profenamine.
The (S)-enantiomer of profenamine.
A trisaccharide derivative consisting of three 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranonosyl units in a linear sequence with an O-allyl group at the anomeric centre.
An adenosine 5'-monophosphate having a salicyl group at the 3'-position; intermediate in mycobactin biosynthesis.
The dimethyl phosphate ester of cardiolipin.
A derivative of cardiolipin having an acetyl group attached to the free hydroxy group of the central glycerol moiety.
The (R)-enantiomer of ethosuximide.
The (S)-enantiomer of ethosuximide.
A cardiolipin derivative in which all four of the phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as oleoyl.
A 7Fe-V-9S-X-homocitryl cluster, the structure of which is assumed to be analogous to the 7Fe-Mo-9S-X-homocitryl cluster. The identity of the X atom is not known, possibly carbon or oxygen.
A derivative of cardiolipin lacking the 2-hydroxy group of the central glycerol moiety.
The (R)-enantiomer of ethotoin.
The (S)-enantiomer of ethotoin.
A D-galactosyl-N-acylsphingosine having a sulfo group at the 3-position on the galactose ring and tetracosanoyl as the N-acyl group.
Lipid IVA glycosylated with three 3-deoxy-D-manno-octulosonic acid (KDO) residues.
Lipid IVA glycosylated with four 3-deoxy-D-manno-octulosonic acid (KDO) residues.
(KDO)-lipid IVA deprotonated at both phosphono groups and at the uronic acid carboxy group.  It is the major species at pH 7.3.
(KDO)2-lipid IVA deprotonated at both phosphono groups and at the uronic acid carboxy groups. It is the major species at pH 7.3.
A D-galactosyl-N-acylsphingosine having a sulfo group at the 3-position on the galactose ring and palmitoyl as the N-acyl group.
(KDO)3-lipid IVA deprotonated at both phosphono groups and at the uronic acid carboxy groups. It is the major species at pH 7.3.
(KDO)4-lipid IVA deprotonated at both phosphono groups and at the uronic acid carboxy groups. It is the major species at pH 7.3.
Trianion of trans,poly-cis-decaprenyl diphosphate arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.

The R-enantiomer of etodolac. It is inactive, in contrast to the enantiomer, (S)-etodolac, which is a preferential inhibitor of cyclo-oxygenase 2 and a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory. The racemate is commonly used for the treatment of rheumatoid arthritis and osteoarthritis, and for the alleviation of postoperative pain.

The S-enantiomer of etodolac. It is a preferential inhibitor of cyclo-oxygenase 2 and a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory, whereas the enantiomer, (R)-etodolac, is inactive. The racemate is commonly used for the treatment of rheumatoid arthritis and osteoarthritis, and for the alleviation of postoperative pain.
A sulfoglycosphingolipid that is sphingosine substituted on O-1 by a 3-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl group; sulfatide in which one acyl chain has been removed by ozonolysis.
Any oxoanion formed by loss of one or more protons from the phosphate groups of a lipid IVA compound.
Trianion of 2-cis,6-cis-farnesyl diphosphate arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A disaccharide derivative consisting of a 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranonosyl residue and a 3-deoxy-7-O-methyl-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranonosyl joined via an alpha-(2->8)-linkage.

An amino tetrasaccharide antigen consisting of two 3-deoxy-D-manno-oct-2-ulose residues and two glucosamine residues (one at the reducing end) in a linear sequence, with two phosphate groups attached.
